# VIATOR — Trivy ignore list
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Comments start with '#'.
# Add an entry only with a written justification, and re-evaluate
# whenever the base image is bumped.
#
# DO NOT blanket-ignore by severity. The CI workflow already passes
# `--ignore-unfixed` (suppress findings with no upstream fix yet) and
# `--severity CRITICAL,HIGH` (ignore noise below HIGH). Anything fixable
# at HIGH or CRITICAL must be addressed, not silenced here.
#
# ── Justified ignores ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The next 6 CVEs are all in Go modules bundled inside the docker CLI
# binary we copy from `docker:29-cli` (see docker/web/Dockerfile stage 1).
# Latest published image (`29.4.1-cli`, 2026-04-21) still ships these
# older bundled deps; we can't patch upstream's binary, only wait for the
# next image rebuild.
#
# Why they're not exploitable in our usage:
#   - The CLI runs as a subprocess inside our `worker` container,
#     invoked only via `docker compose run --rm otp-build` and similar.
#   - It connects to /var/run/docker.sock (Unix socket, host docker
#     daemon — see docker-compose.yml `worker.volumes`). Not network.
#   - Nothing in our codebase exposes the CLI to remote callers, mounts
#     it into untrusted containers, or accepts user input as CLI args.
#   - Auth-bypass / TLS-handshake / DoS CVEs in bundled libs only
#     matter if the binary speaks those protocols to untrusted peers.
#     A subprocess talking to a local socket doesn't.
#
# Re-evaluate when the docker:29-cli image is rebuilt with patched deps,
# or when we bump to docker:30-cli.
#
CVE-2026-34040   # github.com/docker/docker — Moby auth bypass (only matters for daemon, not CLI subprocess)
CVE-2026-35469   # github.com/moby/spdystream — Kubelet/CRI-O issue, irrelevant in CLI
CVE-2026-39883   # go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk — BSD kenv path; we don't run on BSD
CVE-2026-32280   # Go stdlib crypto/x509 — DoS via crafted cert; CLI doesn't accept untrusted certs
CVE-2026-32281   # Go stdlib crypto/x509 — same exposure profile as -32280
CVE-2026-32283   # Go stdlib crypto/tls — multiple key-update DoS; same as -32280
